{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"whats-in-this-tutorial\"><a href=\"#whats-in-this-tutorial\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What‚Äôs in this tutorial?</h2>\n<p>In this tutorial, you‚Äôll be learning about how to pull data into your Gatsby site using GraphQL and source plugins. Before you learn about these plugins, however, you‚Äôll want to know how to use something called Graph<em>i</em>QL, a tool that helps you structure your queries correctly.</p>\n<h2 id=\"introducing-graphiql\"><a href=\"#introducing-graphiql\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Introducing Graph<em>i</em>QL</h2>\n<p>Graph<em>i</em>QL is the GraphQL integrated development environment (IDE). It‚Äôs a powerful (and all-around awesome) tool\nyou‚Äôll use often while building Gatsby websites.</p>\n<p>You can access it when your site‚Äôs development server is running‚Äînormally at\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8000/___graphql\">http://localhost:8000/___graphql</a>.</p>\n<video controls=\"controls\" autoplay=\"true\" loop=\"true\">\n  <source type=\"video/mp4\" src=\"/graphiql-explore.mp4\"></source>\n  <p>Your browser does not support the video element.</p>\n</video>\n<p>Here you poke around the built-in <code class=\"language-text\">Site</code> ‚Äútype‚Äù and see what fields are available\non it‚Äîincluding the <code class=\"language-text\">siteMetadata</code> object you queried earlier. Try opening\nGraph<em>i</em>QL and play with your data! Press <kbd>Ctrl + Space</kbd> to bring up\nthe autocomplete window and <kbd>Ctrl + Enter</kbd> to run the query. You‚Äôll be\nusing Graph<em>i</em>QL a lot more through the remainder of the tutorial.</p>\n<h2 id=\"source-plugins\"><a href=\"#source-plugins\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Source plugins</h2>\n<p>Data in Gatsby sites can come from anywhere: APIs, databases, CMSs,\nlocal files, etc.</p>\n<p>Source plugins fetch data from their source. E.g. the filesystem source plugin\nknows how to fetch data from the file system. The WordPress plugin knows how to\nfetch data from the WordPress API.</p>\n<p>Let‚Äôs add <a href=\"/packages/gatsby-source-filesystem/\"><code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-source-filesystem</code></a> and\nexplore how it works.</p>\n<p>First install the plugin at the root of the project:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\">\n      <pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\">npm install --save gatsby-source-filesystem</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Then add it to your <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-config.js</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\">\n      <pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">module<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>exports <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  siteMetadata<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    title<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`Pandas Eating Lots`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  plugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n<span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n</span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">      resolve<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`gatsby-source-filesystem`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n</span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">      options<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n</span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">        name<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`src`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n</span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">        path<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`</span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>__dirname<span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\">/src/`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n</span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">      <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n</span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n</span>    <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`gatsby-plugin-emotion`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      resolve<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`gatsby-plugin-typography`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      options<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        pathToConfigModule<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`src/utils/typography`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Save that and restart the gatsby development server. Then open up Graph<em>i</em>QL\nagain.</p>\n<p>If you bring up the autocomplete window, you‚Äôll see:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/graphiql-filesystem-58fd47743994afe6ec4c714a53453695-5b1c4.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 786px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 62.72401433691756%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px #ffffff;\"\n        alt=\"graphiql-filesystem\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/graphiql-filesystem-58fd47743994afe6ec4c714a53453695-c4266.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/graphiql-filesystem-58fd47743994afe6ec4c714a53453695-4fd5b.png 197w,\n/static/graphiql-filesystem-58fd47743994afe6ec4c714a53453695-4fc86.png 393w,\n/static/graphiql-filesystem-58fd47743994afe6ec4c714a53453695-c4266.png 786w,\n/static/graphiql-filesystem-58fd47743994afe6ec4c714a53453695-5b1c4.png 1116w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Hit <kbd>Enter</kbd> on <code class=\"language-text\">allFile</code> then type <kbd>Ctrl + Enter</kbd> to run a\nquery.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/filesystem-query-c3247954e5e0325032e945f847611d92-acb38.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 786px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 72.97297297297297%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px #ffffff;\"\n        alt=\"filesystem-query\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/filesystem-query-c3247954e5e0325032e945f847611d92-c4266.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/filesystem-query-c3247954e5e0325032e945f847611d92-4fd5b.png 197w,\n/static/filesystem-query-c3247954e5e0325032e945f847611d92-4fc86.png 393w,\n/static/filesystem-query-c3247954e5e0325032e945f847611d92-c4266.png 786w,\n/static/filesystem-query-c3247954e5e0325032e945f847611d92-22348.png 1179w,\n/static/filesystem-query-c3247954e5e0325032e945f847611d92-f35d4.png 1572w,\n/static/filesystem-query-c3247954e5e0325032e945f847611d92-acb38.png 1850w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Delete the <code class=\"language-text\">id</code> from the query and bring up the autocomplete again (<kbd>Ctrl +\nSpace</kbd>).</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/filesystem-autocomplete-2962bc394bc6ed177276cde5db5ce6b1-acb38.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 786px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 72.97297297297297%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px #ffffff;\"\n        alt=\"filesystem-autocomplete\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/filesystem-autocomplete-2962bc394bc6ed177276cde5db5ce6b1-c4266.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/filesystem-autocomplete-2962bc394bc6ed177276cde5db5ce6b1-4fd5b.png 197w,\n/static/filesystem-autocomplete-2962bc394bc6ed177276cde5db5ce6b1-4fc86.png 393w,\n/static/filesystem-autocomplete-2962bc394bc6ed177276cde5db5ce6b1-c4266.png 786w,\n/static/filesystem-autocomplete-2962bc394bc6ed177276cde5db5ce6b1-22348.png 1179w,\n/static/filesystem-autocomplete-2962bc394bc6ed177276cde5db5ce6b1-f35d4.png 1572w,\n/static/filesystem-autocomplete-2962bc394bc6ed177276cde5db5ce6b1-acb38.png 1850w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Try adding a number of fields to your query, pressing <kbd>Ctrl + Enter</kbd>\neach time to re-run the query. You‚Äôll see something like this:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/allfile-query-b48a3d23278afabbd368b1c2634c73f3-acb38.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 786px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 72.97297297297297%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px #ffffff;\"\n        alt=\"allfile-query\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/allfile-query-b48a3d23278afabbd368b1c2634c73f3-c4266.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/allfile-query-b48a3d23278afabbd368b1c2634c73f3-4fd5b.png 197w,\n/static/allfile-query-b48a3d23278afabbd368b1c2634c73f3-4fc86.png 393w,\n/static/allfile-query-b48a3d23278afabbd368b1c2634c73f3-c4266.png 786w,\n/static/allfile-query-b48a3d23278afabbd368b1c2634c73f3-22348.png 1179w,\n/static/allfile-query-b48a3d23278afabbd368b1c2634c73f3-f35d4.png 1572w,\n/static/allfile-query-b48a3d23278afabbd368b1c2634c73f3-acb38.png 1850w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The result is an array of File ‚Äúnodes‚Äù (node is a fancy name for an object in a\n‚Äúgraph‚Äù). Each File object has the fields you queried for.</p>\n<h2 id=\"build-a-page-with-a-graphql-query\"><a href=\"#build-a-page-with-a-graphql-query\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Build a page with a GraphQL query</h2>\n<p>Building new pages with Gatsby often starts in Graph<em>i</em>QL. You first sketch out\nthe data query by playing in Graph<em>i</em>QL then copy this to a React page component\nto start building the UI.</p>\n<p>Let‚Äôs try this.</p>\n<p>Create a new file at <code class=\"language-text\">src/pages/my-files.js</code> with the <code class=\"language-text\">allFile</code> query you just\ncreated:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\">\n      <pre class=\"language-jsx\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> graphql <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"gatsby\"</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Layout <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"../components/layout\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> data <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n<span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n</span>  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Layout</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n      <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Hello world<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>Layout</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> query <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> graphql<span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`\n  query {\n    allFile {\n      edges {\n        node {\n          relativePath\n          prettySize\n          extension\n          birthTime(fromNow: true)\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n`</span></span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">console.log(data)</code> line is highlighted above. It‚Äôs often helpful when\ncreating a new component to console out the data you‚Äôre getting from the query\nso you can explore the data in your browser console while building the UI.</p>\n<p>If you visit the new page at <code class=\"language-text\">/my-files/</code> and open up your browser console\nyou will see something like:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/data-in-console-3fd681a2f33d483a82d067b07704f7e5-90960.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 786px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 88.56548856548856%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px #ffffff;\"\n        alt=\"data-in-console\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/data-in-console-3fd681a2f33d483a82d067b07704f7e5-c4266.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/data-in-console-3fd681a2f33d483a82d067b07704f7e5-4fd5b.png 197w,\n/static/data-in-console-3fd681a2f33d483a82d067b07704f7e5-4fc86.png 393w,\n/static/data-in-console-3fd681a2f33d483a82d067b07704f7e5-c4266.png 786w,\n/static/data-in-console-3fd681a2f33d483a82d067b07704f7e5-90960.png 962w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The shape of the data matches the shape of the query.</p>\n<p>Let‚Äôs add some code to your component to print out the File data.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\">\n      <pre class=\"language-jsx\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> graphql <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"gatsby\"</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Layout <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"../components/layout\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> data <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Layout</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">      <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n</span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>My Site's Files<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n</span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>table</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n</span><span 